Package: CETYGO
Title: Quantifying the accuracy of cellular deconvolution 
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Eilis", "Hannon", , "e.j.hannon@exeter.ac.uk", role = c("cre", "aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6840-072X")),
		person("Dorethea", "Seiler Vellame", role = c("aut")))
Description: A package to quantify the CETYGO (CEll TYpe deconvolution GOodness) score 
   for cellular deconvolution estimates calcuated using Houseman's reference based deconvolution method. 
   Extends functionality in minfi package and therefore is primarily deisgned for analysis of DNA 
   methlytaion datasets generated with Illumina microarrays. Additioanlly provides functions to perform simulations to assess the
   accuracy of new cell type reference panels.
